                                "Your next stop is at the Museum of Cham Sculpture, which showcases the world's largest collection of Cham artefacts and artworks. As you browse incredible sculptures, learn from your guide about the Champa Kingdom, which reigned in southern Vietnam from 192 to 1697 AD, and identify the Hindu motifs that define Cham architecture.\n" +
                                "After the museum, head finally to Con Market, first established in the 1940s in the heart of Da Nang. Absorb the bustle of local life as you stroll through the outdoor market, and get the chance to try freshly made local specialties from tempting stalls before cycling back to your hotel."
